bake /beɪk/

(baking,baked,bakes) 

1. V-T/V-I If you bake , you spend some time preparing and mixing together ingredients to make bread, cakes, pies, or other food which is cooked in the oven. 烤制 (面包等食品) [no passive] 

例： How did you learn to bake cakes? 你是怎么学会烤蛋糕的？ 

例： I love to bake. 我喜欢烤点心。 

2. baking N-UNCOUNT 烘烤 [also 'the' N] 

例： On a Thursday she used to do all the baking. 她以前每个星期四做所有烘烤的活儿。 

3. V-T/V-I When a cake or bread bakes or when you bake it, it cooks in the oven without any extra liquid or fat. (指蛋糕或面包) 烘烤 

例： Bake the cake for 35 to 50 minutes. 把蛋糕烘烤35至50分钟。 

例： The batter rises as it bakes. 面糊烘烤时膨胀。 

